CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier, October 31, 1959, pg. B2 reads: "Donate Life Membership - Mrs. R.L. Hand, president of the Anna S. Posey Club, holds a check for $150, as the club's first payment on an NAACP life membership. Shown with Mrs. Hand is Mrs. Doris Mixon, the club's financial secretary.  Other officers of the club are: Mrs. Corrine Hunter, vice president; Mrs. Dolores Williams, recording secretary; Mrs. Obessa Bussey, corresponding [sic] secretary; Mrs. Edna Wallace, treasurer, and Mrs. Cora Davis, chaplain."
TitMainTitle: Anna S. Posey Club members Mrs. R. L. Hand holding NAACP lifetime membership check, and Doris Mixon, standing in church interior with stained glass window
